cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for natural image super-resolution using a combination of traditional interpolation techniques and convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of the architecture and the use of skip connections, which are common techniques in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also reports results on standard datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
